1999-10-24  Kai Krueger  <krueger@eowyn>

	* src/tools/Makefile.real: Added missing libraries for fixtai

	* lib/util/rbl_match.c: New format for rbl-type

	* lib/table/tb_test.c: Added table type 'test' as sample

	* lib/table/tb_regexp.c:
	 Added Files:
	 	lib/table/tb_regexp.c
		* Added new table type 'regexp' for key as regular
		  expressions. This table is read sequencialy and each line is
		  matched as regular expression with the search key.

	* lib/table/tb_nis.c: Moved table type 'nis' into new format

	* lib/table/tb_ns.c: Moved table type 'ns' into new format

	* lib/table/Makefile.real, lib/table/table_test.c:
	Added test-programm for check new table-access functions

	* lib/table/ch_tbdbm.c, lib/table/dm_table.c, man/man3/tables.3, src/tools/checkup.c, src/tools/dbmbuild.c, src/tools/fixtai.c, src/tools/tablelist.c, configure.in, h/ch.h, h/config.h.in, lib/mmdf/mm_tai.c, README.devel, Version, configure:
	 Modified Files:
	 	Version configure configure.in h/ch.h h/config.h.in
	 	lib/mmdf/mm_tai.c lib/table/ch_tbdbm.c lib/table/dm_table.c
	 	src/tools/checkup.c src/tools/dbmbuild.c src/tools/fixtai.c
	 	src/tools/tablelist.c
	 Added Files:
	 	README.devel man/man3/tables.3
		* major rewrite of the table-acces functions.
		* both sequencial and dbm access can now coexist
		* Added fetch() and tailoring() functions for tabletype
		  specific access.
		* Now easer to implement new table formats
		* Changes needed by other programs
		* tailoring variable 'flags' no longer for tabletype used
		* new tailoring variable 'type' to define the tabletype

