	* src/smtp/smtpsrvr.c:
		* src/smtp/smtpsrvr.c: John Romine <jromine@yoyodyne.ics.uci.edu>
		  There's a boundary-condition bug in smtpsrvr.c.  If
		  you send an SMTP body with a line of 601 characters
		  where character 601 is a ".", the DATA command is
		  terminated prematurely.
		  Here's an (ugly) fix.

	* lib/util/getllog.bsd.c, lib/util/getllog.c, lib/util/getllog.v7.c, lib/util/getutmp.c, lib/util/tty_io.c, src/tools/checkque.c:
	Added include <utmpx.h>

