1998-07-14  Kai Krueger  <krueger@eowyn>

	* lib/mmdf/alias.c, src/prog/pr2mm_send.c, src/smtp/sm_wtmail.c, src/submit/submit.c, src/tools/checkup.c, uip/snd/alias.c, uip/snd/s.h, uip/snd/s_externs.h, uip/snd/s_get.c, uip/snd/s_input.c:
	 	uip/snd/s_input.c uip/snd/s_get.c uip/snd/s_externs.h
	 	uip/snd/s.h uip/snd/alias.c src/tools/checkup.c
	 	src/submit/submit.c src/smtp/sm_wtmail.c src/prog/pr2mm_send.c
	 	lib/mmdf/alias.c
	        changes for freebsd3.0 made by  Mike Muuss <mike@@arl.mil>
	        1)  diffs.src:  A context diff patch file to be applied to the sources.
	        This contains everything I needed to do in order to get it to compile,
	        plus my extensions to the SND program from 1994 to support "sign" and
	        "encrypt" type operations, either with PGP or another outboard program.
	        It's just a few lines, hopefully it won't get lost from the master
	        sources again.

	* lib/mmdf/alias.c, lib/util/ll_err.c, src/prog/pr2mm_send.c, src/smtp/sm_wtmail.c, src/submit/submit.c, src/tools/checkup.c, uip/snd/alias.c, uip/snd/s.h, uip/snd/s_externs.h, uip/snd/s_get.c, uip/snd/s_input.c:
	 	uip/snd/s_input.c uip/snd/s_get.c uip/snd/s_externs.h
	 	uip/snd/s.h uip/snd/alias.c src/tools/checkup.c
	 	src/submit/submit.c src/smtp/sm_wtmail.c src/prog/pr2mm_send.c
	 	lib/util/ll_err.c lib/mmdf/alias.c
		changes for freebsd3.0 made by  Mike Muuss <mike@arl.mil>
		1)  diffs.src:  A context diff patch file to be applied to the sources.
		This contains everything I needed to do in order to get it to compile,
		plus my extensions to the SND program from 1994 to support "sign" and
		"encrypt" type operations, either with PGP or another outboard program.
		It's just a few lines, hopefully it won't get lost from the master
		sources again.

1998-07-13  Kai Krueger  <krueger@eowyn>

	* conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/s_tailor.h, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/s_tailor.c, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/d_lock.h, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/msgtailor.c, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/config.h, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/conf_dial.c, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/conf.h, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/conf.c, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/chan.c:
	 	chan.c conf.c conf.h conf_dial.c config.h d_lock.h msgtailor.c
	 	s_tailor.c s_tailor.h
		thanks to Mike Muuss <mike@arl.mil>
		3)  freebsd.shar: A SHAR shell archive of the
		conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/ directory. This mostly tracks your
		configuration.  The one important change is that the
		definition of NMSGS in msgtailor.c in the non-pdp11 case needs
		to be increased to something large, like 5000.  This should be
		done for all the provided configurations.

	* conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/s_tailor.h: New file.

	* conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/s_tailor.c:
