	* conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/conf.c, conf/i386-unknown-freebsd3.0/chan.c:
	New file.

	* h/mmdf.h, src/submit/adr_submit.c, src/submit/submit.c, lib/mmdf/rp_valstr.c:
	 	lib/mmdf/rp_valstr.c src/submit/submit.c
	 	src/submit/adr_submit.c h/mmdf.h
		Added new error-codes for checking sender-address at time when
		submit is started
		1)	RP_BADR: unable to send to that address (unable to
		  find a channel to send to) e.g. xxx@com only matches to
		  badhost-channel. If no 'badhost'-channel configured, RP_BADR
		  is returned.

		2)	if wanted, check of incoming-channel and possible
		  outgoing-channel for sender-address is made. If the
		  channel don;t match RP_BCHN is returned.

	* src/smtp/smtpsrvr.c: 	src/smtp/smtpsrvr.c
		Added basics for ESMTP-support, but ESMTP functionality must
		still be implemented. It's just a preparartion for it!

	* uip/other/checkmail.c: fixed option-list

